#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pi-tv-bu-vb-pc49"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr ""

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:0.3"
msgid "Pācittiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on confession (_pācittiya_)"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:0.4"
msgid "Acelakavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 49"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:0.5"
msgid "49. Senāvāsasikkhāpada"
msgstr "The training rule on staying with armies"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-vp-pli4.106, pts-cs-bu-pc49.1, pts-vp-en.2.377, ms2V_995 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sati karaṇīye senaṃ gantvā atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasanti."
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six went to the army on some business, and they stayed there for more than three nights."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.3"
msgid "Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "People complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā senāya vasissanti."
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics stay with the army?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.5"
msgid "Amhākampi alābhā, amhākampi dulladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ ājīvassa hetu puttadārassa kāraṇā senāya paṭivasāmā”ti."
msgstr "It’s our misfortune that we must stay with the army for the sake of our livelihood and because of our wives and children.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms2V_996 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.6"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of those people,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.7"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.8"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.9"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasissantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six stay with the army for more than three nights?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.10"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasathā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.11"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.12"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.13"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasissatha."
msgstr "Foolish men, how can you stay with the army for more than three nights?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.15"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.15a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule">
#. VAR: dirattatirattaṃ → dviratta … (s1-3, pts1)
#. REF: sc3, ms2V_997
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.16"
msgid "“Siyā ca tassa bhikkhuno kocideva paccayo senaṃ gamanāya, dirattatirattaṃ tena bhikkhunā senāya vasitabbaṃ."
msgstr "‘If that monk has a reason for going to the army, he may stay with the army for two or three nights."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:1.17"
msgid "Tato ce uttari vaseyya, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "If he stays longer than that, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc4, pts-cs-bu-pc49.2.1, ms2V_998
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.1.1"
msgid "Siyā ca tassa bhikkhuno kocideva paccayo senaṃ gamanāyāti"
msgstr "If that monk has a reason for going to the army:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.1.2"
msgid "siyā paccayo siyā karaṇīyaṃ."
msgstr "if he has a reason, if he has business."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc5, pts-vp-en.2.378, ms2V_999
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.1.3"
msgid "Dirattatirattaṃ tena bhikkhunā senāya vasitabbanti"
msgstr "He may stay with the army for two or three nights:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.1.4"
msgid "dvetisso rattiyo vasitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may stay for two or for three nights."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term">
#. REF: sc6, ms2V_1000
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.1.5"
msgid "Tato ce uttari vaseyyāti"
msgstr "If he stays longer than that:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.1.6"
msgid "catutthe divase atthaṅgate sūriye senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "if he is staying with the army at sunset on the fourth day, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc7, pts-cs-bu-pc49.2.2, ms2V_1001 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.2.1"
msgid "Atirekatiratte atirekasaññī senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is more than three nights, and he perceives it as more, and he is staying with the army, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.2.2"
msgid "Atirekatiratte vematiko senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is more than three nights, but he is unsure if it is, and he is staying with the army, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.2.3"
msgid "Atirekatiratte ūnakasaññī senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "If it is more than three nights, but he perceives it as less, and he is staying with the army, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8, ms2V_1002 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.2.4"
msgid "Ūnakatiratte atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than three nights, but he perceives it as more, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.2.5"
msgid "Ūnakatiratte vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is less than three nights, but he is unsure if it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.2.6"
msgid "Ūnakatiratte ūnakasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is less than three nights, and he perceives it as less, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc9, pts-vp-pli4.107, pts-cs-bu-pc49.2.3, ms2V_1003 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.2"
msgid "dvetisso rattiyo vasati,"
msgstr "if he stays for two or three nights;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.3"
msgid "ūnakadvetisso rattiyo vasati,"
msgstr "if he stays for less than two or three nights;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.4"
msgid "dve rattiyo vasitvā tatiyāya rattiyā purāruṇā nikkhamitvā puna vasati,"
msgstr "if he stays for two nights, then leaves before dawn on the third night, and then stays again;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.5"
msgid "gilāno vasati,"
msgstr "if he stays because he is sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.6"
msgid "gilānassa karaṇīyena vasati,"
msgstr "if he stays because there is something to be done for someone who is sick;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.7"
msgid "senā vā paṭisenāya ruddhā hoti,"
msgstr " if the army is obstructed by an enemy army;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.8"
msgid "kenaci palibuddho hoti,"
msgstr "if he is obstructed from leaving;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.9"
msgid "āpadāsu,"
msgstr "if there are dangers;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.10"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.11"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc10, ms2V_1004 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc49:2.3.12"
msgid "Senāvāsasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ."
msgstr "The ninth rule, the training rule on staying with armies, is finished."


